. <br>
<br>
As for the casters. Most good wizes/necs/mages will never take a hit, Chanters/Secondary healers tho will often get something aggroed on them in multi mob fights. Adding a little extra AC to them can't hurt if you have the mana. I personally always symbol/AoF the druid I group with regurlary just because I know how pissed off mobs get when you heal. <br>
<br>
 <p>Yurian Stonebow<br>
Purple People Healer<br>
Officer of Blood Reign<br>
Saryrn<br>
<img src="http://www.backpackadventures.com/images/body.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/uandvarishadowmist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AndvariShadowmist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#6FB8DD>(8/14/00 9:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Yupp</span><hr size=1> I have to agree with Yurian (even though I am not a Cleric). AC = God for any melee class and as he said, might be the difference between a cheal and a corpse (and rez is not exactly mana efficient.. just ask the clerics that rezed me 6 times last night). I can clearly notice the difference between the buffs when I do crowd control and get agroed on frequently.<br>
<br>
Andy the Omnipotent <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=garbhad>Garbhad</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Brainbender</span><br>   <font color=#6FB8DD>(8/15/00 1:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yupp</span><hr size=1> Aye AC is god, i am usually the enchanter that yurian is grouped with, and lord knows an enchanter aggroes a mob faster than a ranger with a 1 delay weapon. I will normally wear ac gear instead of mana gear if i am in an area where i know i will definitely get smacked in ( aka sebelis or the hole ) During that time i usually use my own ac buff and hp/ac buff along with the cleric hp buffs and augmentation and my ac gear. With that i can easily reach 675 ac...for a caster thats damn good especially when i still remain at 200int and 200 cha.<br>
<br>
Aof is nice for secondary healers and such like yurian said but i would always SoW the main tank if i were to play a cleric. <p><b>
